headline: How the Narrative Surrounding Intuit Is Changing After the OpenAI Deal and Credit Karma Momentum
summary: Intuit's stock narrative is evolving as analysts tweak their models, keeping fair value steady at roughly $805 per share while nudging the assumed discount rate up from about 8.50% to 8.58% and long term revenue growth from roughly 12.77% to 12.79%. These fine tuned shifts reflect growing conviction in the upside from Intuit's OpenAI partnership and Credit Karma momentum, while also recognizing higher capital costs and execution risks.
